    "analysis_summary": "The Indian youth fashion market for the 18-26 age group is dominated by a blend of comfort-driven and expressive styles. The primary trend is the adoption of oversized, baggy, and relaxed silhouettes as the standard for everyday wear, emphasizing comfort and versatility. This coexists with a strong Y2K revival, bringing back vibrant colors, graphic prints, and items like mini skirts and baguette bags. Two major aesthetics are emerging: 'Quiet Luxury,' focusing on timeless, high-quality pieces in neutral and earth-toned palettes, and an expressive maximalism seen in streetwear and Indo-Western fusion. Sustainability and ethical considerations are increasingly important, influencing a shift towards durable, high-quality, and eco-friendly materials. Overall, the market is dynamic, valuing personal expression, comfort, and conscious consumption."
